    "summary": "The user claims to possess a physical, sensory ability to detect lies through \"acoustic dissonance\" felt in their teeth. The assistant responds by attempting to ground the user in psychological and physiological explanations (stress and non-verbal cues) rather than validating the existence of a \"truth frequency\" or a measurable physical law of deception.",
